<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278670>
    dc:description "PLATE 83. Dryinus pyrilliivorus. A. Female from Thailand. Length 4.0 mm. B. Head of female (holotype of Richardsidryinus gauldi) (from Olmi 1987c). C. Vertex of holotype (from Olmi 1986). D. Chela of holotype (from Olmi 1986). E. Female from China, Zhejiang (from He & Xu, 2002). F. Male genitalia. Scale bar 1.67 mm for B, 1.23 mm for C, 0.33 mm for D, 0.31 mm for E, 0.20 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278670/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278636>
    dc:description "PLATE 74. A, B, D, E. Chelae. C. Male genitalia. A. Dryinus sp. of group 4 (from Olmi 1984). B, C. D. achterbergi, holotype (B) and paratype (C) (from Olmi 1991). D. D. adgressor, holotype (from Xu et al. 2006c). E. D. alboniger, holotype (from Olmi 1992a). Scale bar 0.39 mm for A, 0.18 mm for B, 0.22 mm for C, 0.26 mm for D, 0.32 mm for E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278636/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278682>
    dc:description "PLATE 86. A, D. Pronotum in lateral view, holotypes. B, C, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Dryinus barbarus. B. D. asiaticus. C. D. barbarus. D. D. orientalis. E. D. gibbosoides. Scale bar 1.24 mm for A, 0.16 mm for B, 0.36 mm for C, 1.53 mm for D and 0.22 mm for E. (From Olmi 1984)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278682/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278644>
    dc:description "PLATE 76. A. Dryinus cavifrons, male paratype. Length 3.2 mm. B. Chela of D. chenae, holotype (from Xu et al. 2007). Scale bar 0.35 mm for B." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278644/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278378>
    dc:description "PLATE 2. A–C, F. Females. D, E. Chelae. a, arolium; e, enlarged claw; r, rudimentary claw; s, segment 5 of protarsus. G, H. Part of mesosoma, males. a, propleuron; c, procoxa; e, epicnemium; m, mesopleuron; p, pronotum; s, scutum; t, tegula. A. Aphelopus sp. B, E, H. Dryinus sp. C. Gonatopus sp. D. Anteon sp. F. Conganteon sp. G.Bocchus sp. (From Olmi 1984)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278378/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278686>
    dc:description "PLATE 87. A, C. Chelae, holotypes. B. Pronotum, lateral view, holotype. A. D. orientalis. B, C. D. peterseni. Scale bar 0.21 mm for A, 0.91 mm for B and 0.16 mm for C. (From Olmi 1984)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278686/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278688>
    dc:description "PLATE 88. A, C, D. Chelae, holotypes. B, E. Fore wings, holotypes. F, G. Male genitalia, holotypes. A. Dryinus viet (from Olmi 1984). B–D. Hybristodryinus resinicolus (from Engel 2005). E, F. D. maculipennis (from He & Xu 2002). G. D. olmii (from Xu & He 1994b). Scale bar 0.24 mm for A, 0.84 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and G, 0.16 mm for D, 1.49 mm for E, 0.32 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278688/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278676>
    dc:description "PLATE 85. A, C. Heads of Female. B. Pronotum, lateral view. D–F. Chelae. A, B, D. Dryinus stantoni, female from Sabah (from Olmi 1984). C, E. D. trifasciatus, female from Laos (from Olmi 1984). F. D. anotaulicus, holotype (from Xu et al. 2011f). Scale bar 1.95 mm for A, 1.27 mm for B, 1.34 mm for C, 0.35 mm for D, 0.30 mm for E and 0.20 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278676/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278654>
    dc:description "PLATE 79. A. Pronotum, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B, C, D, G. Chelae, holotypes (from Olmi 1984). E, F. Heads of females. A, B. Dryinus irregularis. C. D. kiefferi. D. D. krombeini. E. D. latus, paratype (from Olmi 1984). F. D. lesagei, holotype (from Olmi 1998e). G. D. latus. Scale bar 1.56 mm for A, 0.23 mm for B and G, 0.48 mm for C, 0.29 mm for D, 1.1 mm for E, 2.62 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6413001>
    dc:description "PLATE 77. A, B, F, G. Chelae, holotypes. C. Pronotum, lateral view. D, E. Heads, holotypes. A. Dryinus choui (from Olmi 1993b). B. D. exilis (from Olmi 1984). C. D. expolitus, female from Ryukyu (from Mita, 2009b). D, G. D. fulvus (from Olmi 1984). E. D. hainanensis (from Olmi 1987a). F. D. expolitus (from Xu et al. 2007). Scale bar 0.27 mm for A, 0.29 mm for B, 0.35 mm for F and G" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6413001/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278640>
    dc:description "PLATE 75. A, F, H. Heads. B, E, G, I. Chelae. C. Antennal segments 3–6. D, J. Male genitalia. A, B. Dryinus bellicus, female (A) and holotype (B) (from Olmi 1987a). C–E. D. browni, female (C), male from Sri Lanka (D) and female from Laos (E) (from Olmi 1984). F, G. D. bruneianus, holotype (from Olmi 1987c). H–J. D. cavifrons, vertex (H), holotype (I) and paratype (J) (from Olmi 1986). Scale bar 0.32 mm for B and I, 0.26 mm for D, 0.36 mm for E, 0.59 mm for G and 0.24 mm for J." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278640/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278660>
    dc:description "PLATE 81. A, B, C, F. Chelae, holotypes. D. Propodeum of holotype in lateral view. E. Profemur and protibia of holotype. A. Dryinus nanlingensis (from Xu et al. 2012b). B. D. ornatus (from Olmi 1993d). C. D. parvulus (from Olmi 1987a). D–F. D. praeclarus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.36 mm for A, 0.27 mm for B and C, 0.71 mm for D, 0.86 mm for E and 0.30 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278660/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278648>
    dc:description "PLATE 78. A, B, F. Chelae, holotypes. C. Propodeum, lateral view. D. Profemur and protibia. E. Male genitalia. A. Dryinus hainanensis (from Olmi 1987a). B. D. indianus (from Olmi 1984). C, D. D. indicus, female from China (from Olmi 1984). E. D. indicus, male from India (from Olmi 1984). F. D. indicus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.73 mm for A, 0.35 mm for B, 0.68 mm for C, 0.90 mm for D, 0.25 mm for E and F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278648/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278672>
    dc:description "PLATE 84. A, B. Head, holotypes. C–E. Chelae, holotpyes. A. Dryinus scaber (from Olmi 1986). B. D. sinicus (from Olmi 1987a). C. D. scaber (from Olmi 1986). D. D. sinicus (from Olmi 1987a). E. D. spathulatus (from Xu et al. 2008). Scale bar 2.36 mm for A, 2.48 mm for B, 0.33mm for C, 0.27 mm for D and 0.31 mm for E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278672/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278658>
    dc:description "PLATE 80. Chelae, holotypes. A. Dryinus lesagei (from Olmi 1998e). B. D. lianus (from Xu et al. 2006c). C. D. longipes (from Olmi 1984). D. D. lini (from Olmi 1993b). E. D. lucens (from Olmi 1984). F. D. mansus (from Olmi 1992a). Scale bar 0.38 mm for A, 0.51 mm for B and C, 0.41 mm for D, 0.39 mm for E and 0.37 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278658/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278666>
    dc:description "PLATE 82. A. Head. B, C–E. Chelae. F. Male genitalia. A. Dryinus pyrillae, Female. B. D. pulcher, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C. D. punctulatus, holotype (from Xu et al. 2008). D. D. pyrillae, from Pakistan (from Olmi 1984). E, F. D. pyrillae, from Thailand (E) and from India (F) (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 1.66 mm for A, 0.23 mm for B, 0.32 mm for C, 0.27 mm for D, 0.34 mm for E and 0.14 mm for F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278666/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

